      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>, <strong>yellow</strong> <strong>mustard seeds</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, a splash of <strong>boiled water </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> to a bowl and stir until dissolved</p><p>Add the<strong> cucumber wedges </strong>to the bowl and give everything a good mix up, then set aside – these are your <strong>quick-pickled cucumber wedges</strong></p><p>Tip: Give the cucumber the occasional shake while pickling</p>",
